SKILL|yvon-settings-patterns|Use when building or modifying YVON OS configuration/settings pages, venture CRUD flows, or any UI that involves cards, tabs, sub-pages, and editable forms. Covers user-preferred UX patterns and the full data pipeline (migration → types → db → API → page).
STEP|1|Building or modifying the Settings page (`app/settings/page.tsx`)
STEP|2|Building venture detail pages (sub-pages under `/settings/venture`)
STEP|3|Adding new fields to the ventures table (profile, socials, deployment, product categories)
STEP|4|User asks to "add a configuration option" or "make something editable"
STEP|5|Modifying the VentureSwitcher, TopBar, or Sidebar (only ONE venture selector allowed)
STEP|6|Settings page uses a **grid of static cards** — no tabs at the top level.
STEP|7|Each card shows read-only status or a small interactive toggle.
STEP|8|Only ONE card links to a detail page: the **Venture card**.
STEP|9|The Venture card is **clickable**. It links to `/settings/venture`.
STEP|10|Inside `/settings/venture`, **sub-tabs are OK**: General, Technical, Social, Deployment.
STEP|11|Each sub-tab is a full section — forms, lists, status panels.
STEP|12|Save buttons use `PATCH /api/ventures/[id]` and refresh data after save.
STEP|13|The TopBar pill (WorkspaceSwitcher) is the **sole** venture selector.
STEP|14|The Sidebar shows a read-only venture badge — no switching from there.
STEP|15|Settings must NOT include a "Switch Venture" section.
STEP|16|The WorkspaceSwitcher fetches ventures from `GET /api/ventures` (Supabase), not `lib/workspaces.ts` hardcoded list.
STEP|17|Each agent card has a **Configure** button that expands a settings panel.
STEP|18|Model selector (8 providers), system prompt extension textarea, Save button.
STEP|19|Saves via `POST /api/settings` per agent per venture.
STEP|20|**Migration** — `supabase/migrations/05X_<name>.sql`
STEP|21|**TypeScript types** — `lib/types.ts`
STEP|22|**DB layer** — `lib/db.ts`
STEP|23|**API route** (usually exists already — `GET/PATCH /api/ventures/[id]` reuse the db functions).
STEP|24|**Frontend page** — `app/settings/venture/page.tsx`
STEP|25|**Settings top level (`/settings`):** Cards only. NEVER tabs.
STEP|26|**Venture detail sub-page (`/settings/venture`):** Sub-tabs ARE allowed (General, Technical, Social, Deployment). This is the one exception — the user accepted sub-tabs inside the detail page because 
STEP|27|If the user says "I don't want tabs," only remove top-level tabs — sub-tabs on detail pages are fine.
STEP|28|Pages MUST NOT wrap content in `max-w-6xl mx-auto` or similar. The `Shell` component already handles page padding (`p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8`). Adding another wrapper creates **double padding** — the user ca
STEP|29|All card grids use `sm:grid-cols-2` — never `sm:grid-cols-1`.
STEP|30|Mobile fallback uses `grid-cols-2` (not `grid-cols-1`). Two cards minimum on every viewport.
STEP|31|Data lives in `venture_socials` table, not `ventures`.
STEP|32|API: `GET /api/ventures/[id]/socials`, `POST /api/ventures/[id]/socials` (upsert).
STEP|33|Frontend: grid of platform cards with `+` to add, `🗑` to remove.
STEP|34|`deploymentPlatforms` is a `TEXT[]` column and a `string[]` in TypeScript.
STEP|35|The frontend uses `DEPLOYMENT_PLATFORMS` constant (12 platforms: Vercel, AWS, Railway, Netlify, Cloudflare, Website, Supabase, Firebase, GA4, Crashlytics, App Store, Play Store, Custom).
STEP|36|Clicking a platform card toggles it on/off via `setDeploymentPlatforms(p => p.includes(id) ? p.filter(...) : [...p, id])`.
STEP|37|Connected platforms show dynamic URL input fields (Vercel domain, GA4 measurement ID, Supabase project ref, etc.).
STEP|38|To add new deployment platform types, add entries to the `DEPLOYMENT_PLATFORMS` array AND add corresponding `{deploymentPlatforms.includes('newId') && (...)}` blocks in the Connection Details section.
STEP|39|**Do NOT wrap `useCallback` in a helper function called during render.** The React rules-of-hooks linter will fail. Instead, define each `useCallback` directly at the component top level:
STEP|40|**Don't duplicate the venture selector.** Only the TopBar pill switches ventures. Never add a second switcher in the Sidebar or Settings page.
STEP|41|**Don't show fake workspaces in the venture pill.** The `WORKSPACES` array in `lib/workspaces.ts` must only contain real ventures (Novizio + Hourbour) — no vibe/canela/valhalla/bydesign. The pill fetc
STEP|42|**Refresh data after save.** After a successful `PATCH`, re-fetch ventures to update the UI state. Don't rely on the patch response alone.
STEP|43|**LocalStorage toggles must hydrate on mount.** All preference toggles need a `useEffect` that reads from localStorage on mount, otherwise the UI flickers to the default state.
STEP|44|**Missing DB column causes silent data loss.** If a field exists in React state but not in the database, it will appear to work in the UI but vanish on every page refresh. The `deploymentPlatforms` fi
STEP|45|The pattern for each tab component:**
STEP|46|Rules:**
STEP|47|All state stays in `page.tsx` (the parent). Components receive values + setters as props.
STEP|48|Extract JSX and logic verbatim — zero visual or behavioral changes.
STEP|49|Private constants that only one tab uses go in that tab's file. Constants needed by multiple components stay in `page.tsx` or extract to a shared file.
STEP|50|`Dispatch<SetStateAction<T>>` is the correct type for React state setters passed as props.
STEP|51|Fix:** Use `task_brief` for titles, `output_content` for descriptions/PR info/QA notes, `agent_id` for agent references. Status values can be any string (no CHECK constraint — defaults to 'complete' b
STEP|52|**ErrorBoundary** — `components/ErrorBoundary.tsx`: Class component wrapping `Shell` in `app/layout.tsx`. Catches any render crash, shows recovery UI with error message + "Try again" + "Reload page" b
STEP|53|**Lighthouse CI** — Install `lighthouse` dev dependency. Add `lighthouse` job to `.github/workflows/ci.yml` that audits 3-5 key pages after build. Store output in `.lighthouse/` directory.
STEP|54|**Bundle Analysis** — Install `@next/bundle-analyzer`. Add `bundle-analyze` job to CI that runs `ANALYZE=true npm run build` and reports chunk sizes.
STEP|55|**Mobile QA** — Add iOS zoom-on-focus fix to `app/globals.css`:
STEP|56|**CI Pipeline Extension** — Full pipeline should be: `lint → typecheck → build → (lighthouse + bundle-analyze) → deploy`. Deploy only triggers on master/main push.
STEP|57|[ ] `tsc --noEmit` passes (0 errors)
STEP|58|[ ] `npx next lint` passes (0 errors, warnings OK)
STEP|59|[ ] No duplicate venture selectors anywhere
STEP|60|[ ] Venture pill only shows 2 ventures (Novizio + Hourbour)
STEP|61|[ ] Settings page has no tabs at the top level — cards only
STEP|62|[ ] Any new DB columns have migration + types.ts + db.ts + API updates
STEP|63|[ ] Save buttons call the correct PATCH/POST endpoint and refresh data
STEP|64|[ ] All toggles persist to localStorage
STEP|65|[ ] ErrorBoundary wraps Shell in layout.tsx
STEP|66|[ ] iOS input font-size fix in globals.css
STEP|67|[ ] Lighthouse + bundle-analyze jobs in CI
STEP|68|[ ] Git commit message describes what changed and why
